description.narrative: UNICEF's earlier investments in strengthening humanitarian-development nexus, the national data systems (DHIS2, mTrac, LMIS), Ebola preparedness and internal health emergency capacities, including staffing, partnership arrangements, supply prepositioning and distribution systems were instrumental to effectively engage with both ‘COVID emergency response' and ‘essential services continuity'. It also helped to reorient UNICEF resources and capacities in support of the Government's response to COVID19. UNICEF played a key role in supporting the COVID19 national and district coordination structures, generating evidence to guide the response, and the adaptation of programme implementation and service delivery modalities. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/08/2020
